@shenyyi Please check it agian in dubbo [3.0-preview](https://github.com/apache/dubbo/tree/3.0-preview)
The initialization process of ReferenceBean has been refactored in Dubbo 3.0. The main purpose is to solve the problem of property injection failure caused by early initialization.
The related pr: https://github.com/apache/dubbo/pull/7383

> Maybe you can use JavaConfig reference dubbo service, like this:
> 
> ```
> @Configuration
> public class DubboServiceReferenceConfig {
> 
>     @DubboReference(version = "${dubbo.application.version}", check = false)
>     private UserInfoService userInfoService;
> 
>     @Bean
>     public UserInfoService userInfoService() {
>         return userInfoService;
>     }
>     
> }
> ```
> 
> Then use @Autowired annotation on your consumer service.

Only need to use @DubboReference to declare and register the reference bean, other places can be injected with `@Autowired`.
 
```java
@Configuration
public class DubboReferenceConfig {

    @DubboReference(version = "${dubbo.application.version}")
    private UserInfoService userInfoService;

    @DubboReference(version = "${dubbo.application.version}")
    private FooService fooService;
    ...
}
```

```java
@Service
public class MyService {
     @Autowired
     private UserInfoService userInfoService;
}
```

